author: @choerrymotion
text:
why â€˜best of meâ€™ is one of btsâ€™ best songs to date: 
a lecture by @choerrymotion lol

this song is incredibly catchy. i mean, i hadnâ€™t heard of bts or â€˜best of meâ€™ yet i somehow knew the chorus. itâ€™s not like other tracks in kpop, it doesnâ€™t condone to the typical kpop sound that is usually seen throughout the genre. that being said, it doesnâ€™t sound westernised either. itâ€™s one of a kind, a song that follows patterns that cannot be repeated. 

not only is the melody great, but the tone in the song is amazing. usually, bts songs are quite high and they do not fit taehyungâ€™s lower vocals as well as they fit jungkookâ€™s higher vocals. however, with this song, taehyungâ€™s vocals fit extremely well as well as jungkook and jiminâ€™s high vocals fitting too. this song has parts where all members can showcase their talents. jin is known to get very few lines yet in this song, it shows that he sings one of the most iconic ones. the rap line have fast paced raps that add to the excitement of the song, namjoon yoongi and hoseokâ€™s verses prove to be a great asset to this b-side. 

lastly, i wanted to talk about the choreography. the choreography is very appealing to watch and fits the song very well. whenever i listen to â€˜best of meâ€™, i can visually imagine bts performing it in my head. during the â€œharuâ€ section that jin sings, bts can be seen walking in a straight line beside each other. this, not only, shows unity but it also fits the dynamic of the music with the dynamic of the movement. 

okay so, thereâ€™s more i could say but you all probably donâ€™t have time, so in conclusion, 
â€˜best of meâ€™ is a masterpiece that is honestly worth your time and recognition. this could be title track material! 

thank you for reading my ted talk on why â€˜best of meâ€™ deserves more. 
@choerrymotion

author: @Raziel8385
text:
Good lord, RM is killing me! Those burning sexy eyes looking right into the camera and into my soul. His dancing is so good now, he's really getting those body rolls and slight movements down now. I'm sure he's been working so hard, and it really shows. He's not so stiff and robotic anymore but when doing the more difficult moves, his face still gets very focused. You can tell he is really thinking about the moves as he does them. I'm so proud of him! And he's just so damn gorgeous lol. Even if his dancing never improved and he wasn't that handsome, he would still be my bias. I absolutely love his voice, the way he conveys emotion and his level of passion. He's a lyrical genius and a master at arranging, mixing, and producing. They say he writes and expresses himself are captivating. Suga is also right up there and it's a pretty close tie, but RM is still my top choice. Even though I love every single member and the beauty and fun that they bring to the group. 
I love you BTS! Thank you for being you and sharing your passion, message and talent with the world. 
Love yourself! Love Myself! 
Stay strong, happy, healthy and safe!

author: @aaliyahdell3488
text: So I had a crazy idea and I know that no one will probably do it, but I at least want to try. BTS has done a lot and is still doing wonders for not just ARMY but people that somewhat know them. A lot of ARMY are showing their gratitude and I want to do so also but not in a money type way. I wanted to write letters but it takes time and money to send letters that may never reach them and I'll probably never meet them, but if anyone wants to join in and help me they can. I wanted to do a hashtag, but I don't have twitter and I don't know how to use it either, so I can't do it there. This is the only way for me to communicate. The hashtag was #BtsInspiresMeTo. It's been 5 years since these boys have debuted (not sure what month) and I want to spread love, so please if you can please spread this hashtag if you'd like. It'd mean a lot to me and even if you don't, thank you for those that read this comment. I guess I'll be the first. #BTSInspiresMeTo lose weight, push myself to the best of my abilities, and to be myself. I'm still trying to find out who I am in this world, and these 7 brothers of ours are really helping. Thank you BTS and a hue thank you to ARMY.

author: @chloehadjard
text:
I saw some people bringing up the fact that they (obviously) used autotune for this performance. Well... of course they did. The song requires powerful and steady vocals and this is near impossible with this choreo, which seems super tiring, without using some autotune. If you don't like the sound of it you can still watch their performance from tbe 4th muster but they don't dance for the whole song.
I don't mean to rant, but people need to understand that BTS are 7 human beings and there are some things that they can't do flawlessly so they need a little help and this time it came in the shape of autotune. Just trying to make a bit of peace.

EDIT: I must admit that the effect was pretty strong here, but the performance was still great and the dancing was on point

Whenever I saw fans crying at concerts , I used to think that it was so stupid. 
But now I know that it's not something you can control if u Stan them so hard. I have been a fan of 1D n other artists but ever since I got to know these 7 dorks, nothing and no one else matters now. I feel all kinds of emotions when I see/hear them. 
I don't know why I cry when I watch their videos(never happened before), no matter what the content is. 
Bangtan is special to me. And I will never allow anyone to take that feeling away from me. They heal me in a way nothing/no one has ever done before... 
If I ever get the chance to see them, all I would ask of them is to never change,never part ways , and always be happy. 
Iam so proud of them and I will always pray for their success...
